@startuml Hedging_IsHedgingCheck
!theme plain
title Hedging Detection - IsHedging Flag Check Logic

start

:Group detected in Process SP\n(GroupID, CustIDList);

:Extract CustIDList from group;

note right
    **Example:**
    CustIDList: "5001,5002,5003"
end note

:Parse CustIDList into Temp_Cust table;

partition "**Customer Classification Check**" {
    :Get latest customer classification\nfor each customer;
    
    note right
        **Query Logic:**
        ```sql
        SELECT CustID, CategoryID, ParentID
        FROM Temp_Cust
        INNER JOIN CTSCustomerClassification
        INNER JOIN CustomerCategory
        WHERE ParentID <> CONST_PARENTID_WRAPPER
        ORDER BY CustomerClassPriority ASC,
                 LastModifiedDate DESC
        LIMIT 1
        ```
        
        **Get highest priority, latest category**
    end note
    
    :Check if customer has PA category\nwith IsHedgingReasonMM = 1;
    
    note right
        **Conditions:**
        1. ParentID = CONST_PARENTID_PA
           (Problem Account parent)
        2. ParentID <> CONST_PARENTID_VVIP
           (Not VVIP)
        3. IsHedgingReasonMM = 1
           (Flagged for hedging detection)
    end note
    
    if (Any customer has IsHedgingReasonMM = 1?) then (yes)
        :Set IsHedging = TRUE;
        
        note right
            **Fast Path:**
            Customer already flagged
            for hedging in category
        end note
        
        :Update Temp_Completed\nSET IsHedging = TRUE;
        
    else (no)
        partition "**Additional Association Check**" {
            :Call SP:\nCTS_DC_Association_IsAssociatedHedgingCustByCustIDList\n(ip_CustIDList, @op_IsHedging);
            
            note right
                **This SP performs:**
                - Historical hedging pattern check
                - Cross-customer hedging association
                - Time-based hedging frequency
                - Multiple match hedging patterns
            end note
            
            if (SP returns IsHedging = TRUE?) then (yes)
                :Set IsHedging = TRUE;
                
                note right
                    **Detected via association:**
                    Customers have hedging history
                    or patterns together
                end note
                
                :Update Temp_Completed\nSET IsHedging = TRUE;
                
            else (no)
                :Set IsHedging = FALSE;
                
                note right
                    **Not Hedging:**
                    - No category flag
                    - No association detected
                    - Group is not suspicious
                end note
                
                :Update Temp_Completed\nSET IsHedging = FALSE;
            endif
        }
    endif
}

:Return IsHedging flag for group;

if (IsHedging = TRUE?) then (yes)
    :Group marked as complete\n(ready to save);
    
    :Will be inserted into\nMatchMonitor & MatchMonitorDetails;
    
else (no)
    :Group filtered out\n(not saved);
    
    :Tickets remain in staging\nfor next iteration;
endif

stop

floating note left
    **IsHedging Flag Flow:**
    
    **Check 1: Customer Classification**
    ↓
    Has IsHedgingReasonMM = 1?
    ├─ YES → IsHedging = TRUE ✓
    └─ NO → Continue to Check 2
    
    **Check 2: Association Check SP**
    ↓
    CTS_DC_Association_IsAssociatedHedgingCustByCustIDList
    ├─ TRUE → IsHedging = TRUE ✓
    └─ FALSE → IsHedging = FALSE ✗
    
    **Final Result:**
    - IsHedging = TRUE → Save to DB
    - IsHedging = FALSE → Discard
end note

floating note right
    **Customer Category Settings:**
    
    **IsHedgingReasonMM Flag:**
    - Set in CustomerCategory table
    - Only for PA (Problem Account) categories
    - Manually configured per category
    
    **Example Categories with Flag:**
    - Category 101: "Hedging Detected"
    - Category 102: "Cross-Platform Hedging"
    - Category 103: "Internal Hedging Pattern"
    
    **CategoryID → IsHedgingReasonMM:**
    - NULL or 0: Not flagged
    - 1: Flagged for hedging detection
end note

@enduml

